		"title": "Memory Persistence & Continuous Learning",
		"desc": "ECC solves Claude Code's native session amnesia through two hook scripts (session-start.js, session-end.js): session startup automatically loads the last saved project state, while session end serializes key decisions, code patterns, and in-progress tasks to disk. On top of this, the continuous-learning-v2 system adds an instinct layer: after each session, evaluate-session.js automatically extracts generalizable behavioral patterns with confidence scores. Developers can browse instincts via /instinct-status, import community instincts with /instinct-import, share their own via /instinct-export, and use /evolve to auto-cluster high-frequency instincts into formal skill files — completing a 'use to learn' flywheel of cross-session knowledge accumulation."
